This paper discusses the formal representation of lexical information for natural language processing (NLP), which is a topic that falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions standardization activities, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL) since standardization can help improve the interoperability and reproducibility of NLP models and algorithms.
